OL,6,F"That means that parents are having to
OL,7,Fpick up the pieces. They're having to
OL,8,Fgive up the work that they love, give
OL,9,Fup their career, to look after their
OL,10,Fchildren."
OL,12,FWe first met Lucas, who has autism and
OL,13,FADHD, and his mother, Joanne Ellis,
OL,14,Ftwo years ago.
OL,16,FHe'd been permanently excluded from
OL,17,Fprimary school in Bradford, at the age
OL,18,Fof five, for lashing out at a teacher
OL,19,Fand was put in a pupil referral unit
OL,20,Fwith teenagers.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/17
