OL,6,FDespite 62% of parents surveyed by the
OL,7,FDCP saying their children have an
OL,8,FEHCP, almost half (47%) said they do
OL,9,Fnot get sufficient support to safely
OL,10,Fcare for their child from education,
OL,11,Fhealth or social care services.
OL,13,FMarsha Martin runs the group Black SEN
OL,14,FMamas, a support network for Black
OL,15,Fmothers of SEND children.
OL,17,FShe is one of those parents who are
OL,18,Fworried about changes to EHCPs. She
OL,19,Ffears the reforms could erode both
OL,20,Fchildren's and parents' legal rights.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/17
